Definition: at or of a point at which a property or phenomenon suffers an abrupt change especially having enough mass to sustain a chain reaction
Example: a critical temperature of water is 100 degrees C--its boiling point at standard atmospheric pressure; critical mass; go critical
Synonyms: noun, state, criticality, NONCRITICAL, cognition, chemistry, c, physics, at, or, of, a, point, which, property, phenomenon, suffers, an, abrupt, change, especially, having, enough, mass, to, sustain, chain, reaction, critical, temperature, water, is, degrees, C--its, boiling, standard, atmospheric, pressure, go
Category: adj.all
